2 Sec. 18701. (1) As used in this part:
3 (a) "Health facility" means a health facility or agency
4 licensed under article 17.
5 (b) "Medical director" means a physician who is responsible
6 for the quality, safety, appropriateness, and effectiveness of the
7 respiratory care services provided by a respiratory therapist, who
8 assists in quality monitoring, protocol development, and competency
9 validation, and who meets all of the following:
10 (i) Is the medical director of an inpatient or outpatient
11 respiratory care service or department within a health facility, or
12 of a home care agency, durable medical equipment company, or
13 educational program.
14 (ii) Has special interest and knowledge in the diagnosis and
15 treatment of cardiopulmonary disorders and diseases.
16 (iii) Is qualified by training or experience, or both, in the
17 management of acute and chronic cardiopulmonary disorders and
18 diseases.
19 (c) "Other qualified practitioner" means any of the following:
20 (i) An advanced practice registered nurse as that term is
21 defined in section 17201 who is acting under the delegation of a
22 physician.
23 (ii) A physician's assistant who is licensed under part 170 or
24 part 175.
25 (d) (c) "Physician" means that term as defined in sections
26 17001 and 17501.
27 (e) (d) "Practice of respiratory care" means the provision of
28 respiratory care services. Practice of respiratory care may be
29 provided by an inpatient or outpatient service or department within
