3
1 a health facility, by a home care agency or durable medical
2 equipment company, or by an educational program.
3 (f) (e) "Respiratory care services" means preventative
4 services, diagnostic services, therapeutic services, and
5 rehabilitative services under the written, verbal, or
6 telecommunicated order of a physician or other qualified
7 practitioner to an individual with a disorder, disease, or
8 abnormality of the cardiopulmonary system as diagnosed by a
9 physician. Respiratory care services involve, but are not limited
10 to, observing, and providing or offering to provide a service
11 involving the evaluation of cardiopulmonary function, the treatment
12 of cardiopulmonary impairment, the assessment of treatment
13 effectiveness, and the care of patients with deficiencies and
14 abnormalities associated with the cardiopulmonary system.
15 Respiratory care services include, but are not limited to, the
16 following:
17 (i) Observing, assessing, and monitoring signs and symptoms,
18 reactions, general behavior, and general physical clinical response
19 of individuals to respiratory care, services, including
20 determination of determining whether those signs, symptoms,
21 reactions, behaviors, or general physical clinical response exhibit
22 abnormal characteristics. ; the
23 (ii) The administration, monitoring, documentation, and
24 instruction of pharmacological, diagnostic, and therapeutic agents
25 related to respiratory care. services; the collection of blood
26 specimens and other bodily fluids and tissues for, and the
27 performance of, cardiopulmonary diagnostic testing procedures
28 including, but not limited to, blood gas analysis;
29 (iii) Obtaining, analyzing, testing, measuring, and monitoring
EMR H02839'25 (H-2) zinws6

4
1 blood and gas samples in the determination of cardiopulmonary
2 parameters and related physiologic data, including, but not limited
3 to, flows, pressures, and volumes, and the use of equipment
4 employed for the purposes described in this subparagraph.
5 (iv) The development, implementation, and modification of
6 respiratory care treatment plans based on assessed abnormalities of
7 the cardiopulmonary system, respiratory care protocols, clinical
8 pathways, referrals, and written, verbal, or telecommunicated
9 orders of a physician or other qualified practitioner. ;
10 application,
11 (v) The application, operation, and management of mechanical
12 ventilatory support and other means of life support. ; and the
13 (vi) Performing cardiopulmonary resuscitation, inserting and
14 maintaining artificial airways and arterial and venous lines, and
15 hemodynamic monitoring.
16 (vii) The initiation of emergency procedures under the rules
17 promulgated by the board.under this part.
18 (viii) Performing therapeutic bronchoscopy, diagnostic
19 bronchoscopy, hyperbaric oxygen therapy, electrophysiological
20 monitoring, and extracorporeal membrane oxygenation.
