2 Sec. 18703. Beginning the effective date of the amendatory act
3 that added this part, an An individual shall not use the titles
4 "respiratory therapist", "respiratory care practitioner", "licensed
5 respiratory therapist", "licensed respiratory care practitioner",
6 "r.t.", "r.c.p.", "l.r.t.", "l.r.c.p.", or similar words that
7 indicate the individual is a respiratory therapist unless the
8 individual is licensed under this article as a respiratory
9 therapist or respiratory care practitioner.
10 Sec. 18707. (1) An individual shall not engage in the practice
11 of respiratory care or provide or offer to provide respiratory care
12 services unless the individual is licensed under this part.
13 (2) Subsection (1) does not prevent any of the following:
14 (a) An individual licensed under any other part or act from
15 performing activities that are considered the practice of
16 respiratory care services if those activities are within the
17 individual's scope of practice and if the individual does not use
18 the titles protected under section 18703.
19 (b) An individual not licensed under this part from performing
20 activities that are considered the practice of respiratory care
21 services while under the supervision of an individual who is
22 licensed under this part as a respiratory therapist or respiratory
23 care practitioner, if the individual does not use the titles
24 protected under section 18703.
25 (c) An individual not licensed under this part from performing
26 activities that are considered diagnostic services if the
27 individual possesses a level of training approved by the board, has
28 successfully passed a credentialing examination approved by the
29 department, in consultation with the board, and if the individual
