13 Sec. 18709. (1) The department, in consultation with the
14 board, shall promulgate rules under section 16145 as necessary or
15 appropriate to fulfill its functions under this article. In
16 promulgating rules to establish requirements for licensure, under
17 section 16145, the department, in consultation with the board,
18 shall adopt all of the following requirements:
19 (a) Successful completion of an accredited respiratory
20 therapist training educational program approved by the department
21 in consultation with the board.
22 (b) Having at least a 2-year associate's associate degree from
23 an accredited college or university approved by the department in
24 consultation with the board.
25 (c) Having the credential conferred by the national board
26 National Board for respiratory care Respiratory Care or its
27 successor organization as a respiratory therapist or its successor
28 credential, as approved by the department in consultation with the
29 board.
