8 Sec. 18710. (1) Beginning 1 year after the effective date of
9 the amendatory act that added this section, an individual who, in
10 addition to meeting the requirements of part 161, meets both of the
11 following requirements must be granted a limited license:
12 (a) Is enrolled and in good standing in a respiratory
13 therapist educational program that meets the requirements described
14 in section 18709(1) or is a graduate of a respiratory therapist
15 educational program that meets the requirements described in
16 section 18709(1).
17 (b) Provides a verification of education form that is
18 completed by the respiratory therapist educational program
19 described in subdivision (a) to the department.
20 (2) All of the following apply to an individual who is granted
21 a limited license under this section:
22 (a) The individual may perform a respiratory care service only
23 if all of the following are met:
24 (i) The individual has successfully completed a course in the
25 educational program described in subsection (1) covering the
26 respiratory care service and the successful completion of the
27 course is documented in the verification of education form
28 described in subsection (1).
29 (ii) The respiratory care service is being provided to a
EMR H02839'25 (H-2) zinws6

9
1 patient who is an adult and who is not a critical care patient.
2 (iii) The individual is acting under the supervision of a
3 respiratory therapist.
4 (b) The individual shall meet at least 1 time each working
5 day, in person, with the respiratory therapist described in
6 subdivision (a) to review the clinical activities of the
7 individual. The respiratory therapist described in subdivision (a)
8 shall provide any redirection or clinical correction during the
9 meeting described in this subdivision and shall review an entry by
10 the individual in a patient's medical record not more than 7 days
11 after the individual makes the entry.
12 (3) A limited license granted under this section expires at
13 the earliest of the following times:
14 (a) One year after the date the limited license is granted.
15 (b) The date the individual becomes licensed under section
16 18709(2)(b).
17 (4) A limited license granted under this section may be
18 renewed once.
19 (5) This section does not require a student meeting the
20 requirements described in section 18707(2)(d) to obtain a limited
21 license under this section.
22 Sec. 18712. (1) Beginning on the effective date prescribed by
23 the department by rule, in addition to the requirements of part
24 161, a licensee seeking renewal of the licensee's license shall
25 furnish the department with satisfactory evidence that, during the
26 licensing period immediately preceding the licensee's application
27 for renewal, the licensee has met 1 of the following conditions:
28 (a) Subject to subsection (3), if the licensee is licensed
29 under section 18709, the licensee completed at least 15 clock hours
EMR H02839'25 (H-2) zinws6

10
1 of continuing education courses that are designed to further
2 educate licensees, as approved by the board.
3 (b) The licensee has successfully passed 1 of the following:
4 (i) A written professional examination administered by the
5 National Board for Respiratory Care, including, but not limited to,
6 the registry examination for advanced respiratory therapists, the
7 recredentialing examination for certified respiratory therapists,
8 the pulmonary function technology examination, the neonatal or
9 pediatric specialty examination, the sleep disorder specialty
10 examination, or an equivalent written professional examination as
11 determined by the board.
12 (ii) The registered polysomnographic technologist examination
13 administered by the Board of Registered Polysomnographic
14 Technologists, the certified asthma education examination
15 administered by the National Asthma Educator Certification Board,
16 or an equivalent examination as determined by the board.
17 (2) As required under section 16204, each applicant for
18 license renewal shall complete as part of the requirements under
19 subsection (1) an appropriate number of hours or courses in pain
20 and symptom management, as prescribed by rule.
21 (3) None of the following meet the continuing education
22 requirement described in subsection (1):
23 (a) A course on basic life support or cardiopulmonary
24 resuscitation.
25 (b) An educational activity if the educational activity has
26 the identical objective and content as another educational activity
27 used for continuing education during the same licensing period
28 immediately preceding the licensee's application for renewal.
29 (c) An employer-specific orientation or in-service program
EMR H02839'25 (H-2) zinws6

11
1 that does not significantly enhance the practice of respiratory
2 care.
3 (d) Self-directed independent study, including, but not
4 limited to, reading a text or journal article that has not been
5 approved by the board.
6 (e) Participation in clinical practice or research if it is
7 not part of a continuing education activity approved by the board.
8 (f) A personal development activity that is not taken for the
9 purposes of meeting a continuing education requirement.
10 (g) A professional meeting or convention unless the meeting or
11 convention or a portion of the meeting or convention is a
12 continuing education activity approved by the board.
13 (h) Community service and volunteer practice.
14 (i) Membership in a professional organization.
15 (j) A contact hour if the licensee is required to complete the
16 contact hour by rule and the contact hour would result in the
17 licensee exceeding the clock hours prescribed in this section.
18 (4) A licensee shall maintain evidence of the licensee's
19 compliance with the requirements of this section for a period of 4
20 years after the date of the licensee's application for renewal,
21 during which time the licensee may be required to submit the
22 evidence for auditing purposes.
23 (5) The department shall promulgate rules to implement this
24 section by 1 year after the effective date of the amendatory act
25 that added this section.
26 (6) As used in this section:
27 (a) "Clock hour" means a period of 50 to 60 minutes.
28 (b) "Contact hour" means a period of 50 to 60 minutes of
29 planned classroom, clinical, or provider-directed independent
